<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-07T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-07T12:00:00-05:00" n="567" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d567">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4598: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1" type="to">Cunningham</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-07T12:00:00-05:00">March 7, 1932—12
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>80. For the Minister. Your March 6, 1 a.m.</p>
                        <p>See Department’s 76, March 4, 11 p.m., paragraphs 1 and 4.</p>
                        <p>What common action taken? What report, if any, made by the <pb facs="0633" n="529" xml:id="pg_529"/> military representatives of
                            the League powers to the League and/or to their respective
                            governments?</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SHL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>